item.description:
Namespace using Declarations A using declaration lets us use a name from a namespace without qualifying the name with a namespace_name::prefix. A using declaration has the form:
using namespace::name;
For example:
#include &lt;iostream&gt;using std::cin; int main() { int i; cin &gt;&gt; i; // ok: cin is a synonym for std::cin cout &lt;&lt; i; // error: no using declaration std::cout &lt;&lt; i; // ok return 0; } Code inside headers ordinarily should not use using declarations.
